# Theme System — Agent Rules

Hobby Warehouse uses a **CSS-variable-based multi-theme system** with 5 themes.
Every new UI component or page MUST follow these rules to remain theme-aware.

## 1. Use Semantic Token Classes — Never Hardcode Colors

**Required** — use these Tailwind utilities (they map to CSS variables):

| Purpose | Class(es) |
|---|---|
| Page background | `bg-canvas` |
| Card / panel background | `bg-surface` |
| Elevated (modal, dropdown) | `bg-overlay` |
| Primary border | `border-rim` |
| Subtle border | `border-rim-subtle` |
| Primary text | `text-fg` |
| Secondary text | `text-fg-muted` |
| Tertiary / placeholder text | `text-fg-subtle` |
| Primary action bg | `bg-accent` |
| Primary action text | `text-accent-fg` |
| Action hover | `bg-accent-hover` / `hover:bg-accent-hover` |
| Subtle accent tint | `bg-accent-muted` / `text-accent` |
| Error background | `bg-danger-muted` |
| Error text | `text-danger-fg` / `text-danger` |
| Success | `text-ok` / `bg-ok` |

**Forbidden** — do not hardcode palette colors in new code:

- `bg-zinc-*`, `text-zinc-*`, `border-zinc-*`
- `bg-emerald-*`, `text-emerald-*` (use `bg-accent`, `text-accent` instead)
- `bg-white`, `bg-black`, `text-white`, `text-black`
- `dark:bg-*`, `dark:text-*`, `dark:border-*` (the theme system handles this)

**Allowed exception:** Tailwind semantic utilities like `rounded-*`, `px-*`, `flex`, `grid`, `w-*`, `h-*`, `font-*`, `opacity-*`, `transition-*`, `z-*`, etc. are always fine.

## 2. For Complex Dynamic Colors — Use CSS Variables Directly

When you need opacity modifiers or gradients, use inline style with CSS variables:

```tsx
// Semi-transparent backgrounds
<div style={{ background: "color-mix(in oklch, var(--surface) 60%, transparent)" }} />

// Gradients
<div style={{ background: "linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent), var(--accent-hover))" }} />

// Glow effects
<div style={{ boxShadow: "0 0 40px var(--glow-accent)" }} />
```

## 3. Adding a New Theme

When you add a brand-new theme:

1. **`web/src/lib/themes.ts`** — add a `ThemeConfig` entry to the `THEMES` array.
   - Set `isDark: true` for dark themes, `false` for light.
   - Fill in the `preview` swatches for the theme selector UI.

2. **`web/src/app/globals.css`** — add a `[data-theme="your-id"]` block with **all** of the following CSS variables defined:

   ```css
   [data-theme="your-id"] {
     --canvas:        /* page background */;
     --surface:       /* card / panel */;
     --overlay:       /* elevated elements */;
     --rim:           /* primary border */;
     --rim-subtle:    /* subtle border */;
     --fg:            /* primary text */;
     --fg-muted:      /* secondary text */;
     --fg-subtle:     /* placeholder / tertiary */;
     --accent:        /* primary CTA color */;
     --accent-hover:  /* accent hover */;
     --accent-fg:     /* text on accent bg */;
     --accent-muted:  /* subtle accent tint */;
     --danger:        /* error color */;
     --danger-hover:  /* error hover */;
     --danger-muted:  /* error bg tint */;
     --danger-fg:     /* text on danger bg */;
     --ok:            /* success color */;
     --sidebar-from:  /* sidebar gradient start */;
     --sidebar-via:   /* sidebar gradient mid */;
     --sidebar-to:    /* sidebar gradient end */;
     --glow-accent:   /* accent ambient glow */;
     --glow-top:      /* top page radial glow */;
   }
   ```

3. The theme will automatically appear in the **ThemeSelector** sidebar widget
   (no further code changes needed there).

## 4. Form Fields — Use `field-classes.ts`

For inputs, labels, buttons, and tables, import from the shared class strings:

```ts
import {
  inputClass,
  labelClass,
  buttonPrimaryClass,
  buttonSecondaryClass,
  buttonDangerClass,
  tableClass,
  thClass,
  tdClass,
  cardClass,
  sectionHeadingClass,
  sectionSubheadingClass,
} from "@/components/forms/field-classes";
```

Never define one-off input/button styles for new form components.

## 5. ThemeProvider is Already Available

The `ThemeProvider` wraps the entire app at `web/src/app/layout.tsx`.
If you need the active theme in a client component, use:

```tsx
"use client";
import { useTheme } from "@/components/providers/ThemeProvider";

const { theme, setTheme } = useTheme();
```

## 6. Icon Colors

Use `style={{ color: "var(--accent)" }}` or `text-fg-muted` on Lucide icons.
Do not use `text-zinc-400`, `text-emerald-500`, etc.
